---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="Deploy Hooks"
  description="Run shell commands on the server before and after each deploy, for migrations, cache clearing, and queue restarts."
  section="features"
>
  <p>
    Deploy hooks let you run arbitrary shell commands on the server as part of the deploy pipeline.
    Hooks execute via SSH in the app's working directory
    (<code>/opt/shuttle/&lt;app&gt;/&lt;app&gt;/</code>), so they have access to your
    <code>.env</code> file and any files deployed with your app.
  </p>

  <h2>Hook types</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Hook</th>
        <th>When it runs</th>
        <th>On failure</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>pre_deploy</code></td>
        <td>After accessories are ensured, before containers are replaced</td>
        <td>Aborts the deploy immediately</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>post_deploy</code></td>
        <td>After all services have been deployed successfully</td>
        <td>Warning only — deploy is marked successful</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">deploy:
  hooks:
    pre_deploy:
      - php artisan migrate --force
      - php artisan db:seed --class=RequiredSeeder

    post_deploy:
      - php artisan cache:clear
      - php artisan config:cache
      - php artisan route:cache
      - php artisan queue:restart
</code></pre>

  <h2>Execution environment</h2>
  <p>
    Each hook command runs in a login shell on the remote host:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">cd /opt/shuttle/&lt;app&gt;/&lt;app&gt; &amp;&amp; /bin/sh -lc "&lt;command&gt;"
</code></pre>
  <p>
    The <code>-l</code> flag loads the login shell profile, making any system PATH entries and
    environment variables available. The working directory is the app directory, which contains the
    <code>.env</code> file uploaded by the secrets step.
  </p>

  <h2>Pre-deploy hook failure</h2>
  <p>
    If a pre-deploy hook exits with a non-zero code, the deploy is aborted immediately. No
    containers are replaced and no proxy changes are made. The deploy lock is released and the
    error is reported:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">pre_deploy hook failed on 203.0.113.10 (exit 1): SQLSTATE[42P07]: Duplicate table: migration already exists
</code></pre>
  <p>
    This makes pre-deploy hooks safe for database migrations — a failed migration will stop the
    deploy before any new code is running.
  </p>

  <h2>Post-deploy hook failure</h2>
  <p>
    Post-deploy hook failures are logged as warnings but do not mark the deploy as failed. This is
    intentional: your new containers are already running and serving traffic. A cache-clear failure
    is a recoverable condition that should not roll back a successful deploy.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you need post-deploy failures to be fatal, move the command to <code>pre_deploy</code> or
    handle it in your application startup.
  </p>

  <h2>Per-host execution</h2>
  <p>
    Hooks run on every host in every server group. If you deploy to 3 web servers,
    <code>php artisan migrate --force</code> runs 3 times. Use application-level idempotency
    (migrations already handle this) or conditional commands to avoid duplicate work:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">deploy:
  hooks:
    pre_deploy:
      # Only run migration if this host holds the "primary" flag file
      - "[ -f /opt/shuttle/my-app/.primary ] && php artisan migrate --force || true"
</code></pre>

  <h2>Common patterns</h2>

  <h3>Laravel</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">deploy:
  hooks:
    pre_deploy:
      - php artisan migrate --force
    post_deploy:
      - php artisan cache:clear
      - php artisan config:cache
      - php artisan route:cache
      - php artisan view:cache
      - php artisan queue:restart
</code></pre>

  <h3>Symfony</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">deploy:
  hooks:
    pre_deploy:
      - php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate --no-interaction
    post_deploy:
      - php bin/console cache:clear --env=prod
      - php bin/console messenger:stop-workers
</code></pre>

  <h3>Node.js</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">deploy:
  hooks:
    pre_deploy:
      - node scripts/migrate.js
    post_deploy:
      - curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/cache/flush
</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
